<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[114,1089,939,1220]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[114,363,939,963]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Owing to the coloration of the pronotum, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk &amp; Zhang, 2006" authorityName="Bezděk &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2006" box="[804,891,940,963]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[804,891,940,963]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">A. yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[896,977,940,963]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles other 
<taxonomicName box="[173,364,972,996]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[173,282,972,996]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Apophylia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with extended black pattern on the pronotum – 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fairmaire, 1888)" baseAuthorityName="Fairmaire" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandicornis">
<emphasis box="[859,1023,972,996]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">A. grandicornis</emphasis>
(Fairmaire, 1888)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezdek, 2003" authorityName="Bezdek" authorityYear="2003" box="[261,512,1004,1028]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frischi">
<emphasis box="[261,358,1004,1028]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">A. frischi</emphasis>
Bezděk, 2003
</taxonomicName>
, and females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Laboissiere, 1927" authorityName="Laboissiere" authorityYear="1927" box="[683,1019,1004,1028]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variicollis">
<emphasis box="[683,820,1004,1028]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">A. variicollis</emphasis>
Laboissière, 1927
</taxonomicName>
. However, all these species have a yellow anterior part of the head (completely black in 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk &amp; Zhang, 2006" authorityName="Bezděk &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2006" box="[966,1053,1036,1059]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi" status="sp. nov.">
